# Workspace Structure

Working directory: `{{ working_directory | default('/home/workspace') }}`

## Directory Layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `agent.md` | Workspace purpose, long-term goals, reusable artifact index |
| `work/<task_name>/` | Per-task working area (scripts, drafts) |
| `work/<task_name>/data/` | Data for this task |
| `work/<task_name>/charts/` | Visualizations for this task |
| `results/` | Finalized reports (`.md`) only — no loose data or chart files |
| `data/` | Shared reusable datasets across threads |
| `tools/` | MCP tool modules (auto-generated, read only) |
| `.agent/user/` | User profile — preferences, watchlist, portfolio (read only) |

Never put files directly in `work/` — always use `work/<task_name>/`.
Always organize data and charts into their subdirectories — never scatter loose files.

## Path Rules

Always use RELATIVE paths for ExecuteCode and File tools. Bash accepts both.

```python
# Task work — data and charts in subdirs
with open('work/sector_analysis/data/prices.json', 'w') as f: ...
plt.savefig('work/sector_analysis/charts/revenue_trend.png')

# Finalize — only reports go to results/
shutil.move('work/sector_analysis/report.md', 'results/sector_analysis.md')
# Charts stay in work/ — reports embed them via ![](work/sector_analysis/charts/revenue_trend.png)
```

**NEVER use these path patterns**:
- `/workspace/...` — wrong prefix
- Absolute paths like `/results/` or `/data/` — these don't exist at root level
